title: Chair with rush seat
inscriptions: verso on plaque: THIS CHAIR/ WAS BROUGHT FROM NORWICH ENGLAND/ IN 1638 BY ROBERT WILLIAMS/ WHO SETTLED IN ROXBURY MASS/ AND DIED IN HATFIELD IN 1698./ IT WAS GIVEN TO HEZEKIAH PORTER,/ OF DALTON BY DOROTHY WILLIAMS/ PRESENTED TO/ WILLIAMS COLLEGE/ BY/ ZENAS MARSHALL CRANE/ ABOUT 1875
